an unleash chaos and conflict, underscoring the interconnectedness and often unintended consequences of divine and mortal actions.\", \"from\": 3637, \"to\": 3829, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her vengeful ploy\", \"from\": 3637, \"to\": 3654}, {\"ngram\": \"a slighted deity's actions\", \"from\": 3671, \"to\": 3697}, {\"ngram\": \"chaos\", \"from\": 3710, \"to\": 3715}, {\"ngram\": \"conflict\", \"from\": 3720, \"to\": 3728}, {\"ngram\": \"the interconnectedness\", \"from\": 3743, \"to\": 3765}, {\"ngram\": \"often unintended consequences\", \"from\": 3770, \"to\": 3799}, {\"ngram\": \"divine and mortal actions\", \"from\": 3803, \"to\": 3828}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Similarly, the Last Supper directly precedes Jesus' arrest, trial, torture, crucifixion, and resurrection.\", \"from\": 3831, \"to\": 3937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3876, \"end\": 3889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arrest_of_Jesus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jesus' arrest\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arrest_of_Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arrest_of_Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 3842, \"to\": 3857}, {\"ngram\": \"trial\", \"from\": 3891, \"to\": 3896}, {\"ngram\": \"torture\", \"from\": 3898, \"to\": 3905}, {\"ngram\": \"crucifixion\", \"from\": 3907, \"to\": 3918}, {\"ngram\": \"resurrection\", \"from\": 3924, \"to\": 3936}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Judas Iscariot, one of the apostles, betrays Jesus for thirty pieces of silver, driven by greed and the love of money.\", \"from\": 3938, \"to\": 4056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3938, \"end\": 3952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judas_Iscariot\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.748076601062719e-75, \"text\": \"Judas Iscariot\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judas_Iscariot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judas_Iscariot\"}, {\"begin\": 3975, \"end\": 3988, \"title\": \"http: